President Trump delivers a speech at the commissioning ceremony of the USS Gerald R. Ford, the newest and largest aircraft carrier in the world. He praises the ship and its crew, and thanks the public servants and officials in attendance. He emphasizes the importance of a strong military and the need for increased funding and support. He also pays tribute to Gerald Ford, the ship's namesake, and highlights the significance of American patriotism and values. The President concludes by officially placing the USS Gerald R. Ford in commission and expressing his wishes for its success and the safety of its crew.